The paper deals with visual search using convolutional neural networks, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a scalable database service for efficient search suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB). The use of satellite and aerial imagery suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of binary feature vectors and hash-based search suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
